<subSubSection id="C33E6576820CFFECFCDAFE5FFB4AC871" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9B36FD820CFFECFCDAFE5FFB4AC871" blockId="1.[793,1422,477,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFCDAFE5FFC2BCAD1" bold="true" box="[794,898,477,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Remarks</emphasis>
. Characters which define the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D7E820CFFECFAD8FE5FFC7AC936" authority="Vassilenko, 1968" authorityName="Vassilenko" authorityYear="1968" class="Malacostraca" family="Phtisicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Phtisicidae 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFCDAFE78FC7AC936" author="Vassilenko, S" box="[794,979,506,530]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="1461 - 1464" refId="ref8892" refString="Vassilenko, S. V. 1968. [On the taxonomy and basic development lines of the family Caprellidae (Amphipoda, Caprellidea)]. Akademiya Nauk SSSR, Doklady 183: 1461 - 1464." type="journal article" year="1968">Vassilenko, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are a fully fused head and pereonite 1, absence of a mandibular molar and 3-articulate palp, gills on pereonites 2–4 (3 pair), pereonites 5 and 6 separated and the urosomites 1 and 2 coalesced (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFB22FDD0FA20C94E" author="Takeuchi, I" box="[1250,1417,594,618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="947 - 964" refId="ref8751" refString="Takeuchi, I. 1993. Is the Caprellidea a monophyletic group? Journal of Natural History, 27: 947 - 964. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939300770581" type="journal article" year="1993">Takeuchi, 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFCDAFDEDFCFAC9A3" author="Takeuchi, I" box="[794,851,623,647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="368 - 373" refId="ref8787" refString="Takeuchi, I. 2015. A new species of Paraproto (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Phtisicidae) collected from the South Shetland Islands, Antarctica. Polar Science 9: 368 - 373. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. polar. 2015.08.002" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFCA1FDEDFBB1C9AC" author="Lim, J" box="[865,1048,623,648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="241 - 251" refId="ref8494" refString="Lim, J. H. C., B. A. R. Azman, and I. Takeuchi. 2012. Microtripus tinggiensis, new genus and species (Amphipoda: Caprellidea: Phtisicidae) from Pulau Tinggi, East Johor Islands Archipelago, Malaysia. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 125 (3): 241 - 251. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2988 / 11 - 40.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Lim 
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFC56FDF2FC61C9A3" box="[918,968,623,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">et al</emphasis>
., 2012
</bibRefCitation>
; Takeuchi and Lowry, 2016). The diagnosis of the genus was based observations of the 
<typeStatus id="549F885F820CFFECFA9FFD0FFA24C981" box="[1375,1421,653,677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D7E820CFFECFC59FD29FB43C9E6" authority="Hirayama, 1988" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1988" box="[921,1258,682,706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Quadrisegmentum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulum">
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFC59FD29FB9AC9E6" box="[921,1075,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Q. triangulum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFBFCFD28FB43C9E6" author="Hirayama, A" box="[1084,1258,682,706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="1089 - 1093" refId="ref8307" refString="Hirayama, A. 1988. A ghost shrimp with four-articulate fifth pereopods (Crustacea: Caprellidea: Phtisicidae) from northwest Australia. Zoological Science 5: 1089 - 1093." type="journal article" year="1988">Hirayama, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the present study with reference to description and figures of mouth parts in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B0C820CFFECFCF7FD67FC59C9D9" author="Hirayama, A" box="[823,1008,741,765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" pagination="1089 - 1093" refId="ref8307" refString="Hirayama, A. 1988. A ghost shrimp with four-articulate fifth pereopods (Crustacea: Caprellidea: Phtisicidae) from northwest Australia. Zoological Science 5: 1089 - 1093." type="journal article" year="1988">Hirayama (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and additionally the two new species described in the current study, 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D7E820CFFECFBB0FC81FB73C83E" authority="Hughes &amp; Takeuchi, 2016" authorityName="Hughes &amp; Takeuchi" authorityYear="2016" box="[1136,1242,771,794]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Quadrisegmentum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atauro" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFBB0FC81FB73C83E" box="[1136,1242,771,794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Q. atauro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2635794820CFFECFB24FC81FA93C83E" box="[1252,1338,771,794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D7E820CFFECFAB3FC81FCC1C813" authority="Hughes &amp; Takeuchi, 2016" authorityName="Hughes &amp; Takeuchi" authorityYear="2016" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Quadrisegmentum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yirrgay" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFAB3FC81FCC1C813" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Q. yirrgay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2635794820CFFECFCAFFCA2FC6DC813" box="[879,964,800,823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(map 
<figureCitation id="131F2A78820CFFECFBCAFC9DFBFFC81C" box="[1034,1110,799,824]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[437,500,935,957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,152,921]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[166,1466,151,922]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution of world species of Quadrisegmentum Hirayama, 1988." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676908/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) provides the distribution of the four known 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D7E820CFFECFC03FCBFFB21C871" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1988" box="[963,1160,829,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Quadrisegmentum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B950EAEF820CFFECFC03FCBFFB21C871" box="[963,1160,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="232">Quadrisegmentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
